  <body>
    <section name="Defining what jars are needed for your application">
      <p>It is possible to use only the genesis binding features without using 
      the empty project that comes with the framework distribution. However, 
      what jars are needed vary depending on features and minimum JRE release to
      be supported. The table below describes requirements for each scenario:</p>
      <table>
         <tr>
            <th>Feature</th>
            <th>Java 1.4</th>
            <th>Java 5</th>
            <th>Java 6</th>
            <th>Notes</th>
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>Binding</td>
            <td colspan="3">
               backport175-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               commons-beanutils-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               commons-logging-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               genesis-client-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               genesis-shared-annotated-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               reusable-components-&lt;version&gt;.jar
            </td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>Annotation support</td>
            <td>genesis-annotation-jdk14-&lt;version&gt;.jar</td>
            <td colspan="2">genesis-annotation-jdk5-&lt;version&gt;.jar</td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>Swing binding</td>
            <td colspan="3">genesis-client-swing-&lt;version&gt;.jar</td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>SWT binding</td>
            <td colspan="3">genesis-client-swt-&lt;version&gt;.jar</td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>Thinlet binding</td>
            <td colspan="3">genesis-client-thinlet-&lt;version&gt;.jar</td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>JavaScript as script language</td>
            <td colspan="2">
               bsf-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               js-&lt;version&gt;.jar
            </td>
            <td>No jar is needed</td>
            <td>This is the default script language</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>BeanShell as script language</td>
            <td colspan="3">
               bsf-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               bsh-&lt;version&gt;.jar
            </td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>EL as script language</td>
            <td colspan="3">
               bsf-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               commons-el-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               jakarta-taglibs-standard-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               jsp-api.jar
            </td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>JXPath as script language</td>
            <td colspan="3">commons-jxpath-&lt;version&gt;.jar</td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>Validation</td>
            <td colspan="3">
               commons-digester-&lt;version&gt;.jar<br />
               commons-validator-&lt;version&gt;.jar
            </td>
            <td />
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>Regular expression-based validation</td>
            <td colspan="3">
               jakarta-oro-&lt;version&gt;.jar
            </td>
            <td><code>email</code> validator, for instance</td>
         </tr>
      </table>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>